.TH "qla4xxx_mailbox_command" 9 "qla4xxx_mailbox_command" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qla4xxx_mailbox_command \- issues mailbox commands
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qla4xxx_mailbox_command
.BI "(struct scsi_qla_host *ha "  ","
.BI "uint8_t inCount "  ","
.BI "uint8_t outCount "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *mbx_cmd "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *mbx_sts "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ha" 12
Pointer to host adapter structure.
.IP "inCount" 12
number of mailbox registers to load.
.IP "outCount" 12
number of mailbox registers to return.
.IP "mbx_cmd" 12
data pointer for mailbox in registers.
.IP "mbx_sts" 12
data pointer for mailbox out registers.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine issue mailbox commands and waits for completion.
If outCount is 0, this routine completes successfully WITHOUT waiting
for the mailbox command to complete.
